From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|helle}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|hel}}, {{m|ang|hell}}, {{m|ang|helle||nether world, abode of the dead, hell}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*haljō||nether world, concealed place}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*ḱel-||to cover, conceal, save}}. Cognate with {{cog|stq|Hälle||hell}}, {{cog|nds-de|Hell||hell}}, {{cog|nl|hel||hell}}, {{cog|de|Hölle||hell}}, {{cog|sv|helvete||hell}}, {{cog|is|hel||the abode of the dead, death}}. Also related to the {{m|en|Hel}} of [[Germanic]] [[mythology]]. See also {{l|en|hele}}.

